00:23:57.813 --> 00:24:00.480
Thank you for earlier.

00:24:03.980 --> 00:24:07.563
How old were you
when you started training, Iroha?

00:24:11.188 --> 00:24:13.688
All of the Kyohachi-ryu
were abandoned as children.

00:24:14.188 --> 00:24:15.855
We don't know our real ages.

00:24:16.438 --> 00:24:19.313
Were there any other girls?

00:24:20.980 --> 00:24:21.896
No.

00:24:23.646 --> 00:24:25.188
I was young

00:24:26.605 --> 00:24:28.063
and the weakest of them all.

00:24:28.646 --> 00:24:29.855
You were the weakest?

00:24:31.230 --> 00:24:32.688
It was a long time ago.

00:24:46.688 --> 00:24:50.771
What should I do to be as strong as you?

00:24:59.730 --> 00:25:01.355
You don't have to…

00:25:02.730 --> 00:25:04.355
and there's no need.

00:25:07.188 --> 00:25:09.396
No matter how skilled
you get at using a sword…

00:25:11.855 --> 00:25:13.480
it won't bring you happiness.

00:25:19.563 --> 00:25:20.438
He's here.

00:25:33.105 --> 00:25:35.646
Ow! That hurts.

00:25:36.146 --> 00:25:38.521
No need to be so rough!

00:25:39.313 --> 00:25:40.813
H-Hello, sir.

00:25:41.313 --> 00:25:43.188
He's the suspect for the teahouse murders.

00:25:43.271 --> 00:25:44.230
You've got it wrong.

00:25:44.313 --> 00:25:45.938
We'll hold him in jail.

00:25:46.021 --> 00:25:46.855
Yes, sir.

00:25:46.938 --> 00:25:48.480
-Let's go!
-Ow, ow!

00:25:55.688 --> 00:25:58.021
I can't wait to see what happens.

00:25:59.688 --> 00:26:01.480
-No!
-Silence!

00:26:01.563 --> 00:26:02.605
POLICE BRANCH OFFICE

00:26:08.480 --> 00:26:11.563
You stay quiet in here.
We'll interrogate you later.

00:26:11.646 --> 00:26:12.688
Hey! Wait.

00:26:13.355 --> 00:26:14.813
Please.

00:26:16.021 --> 00:26:17.188
What about a guard?

00:26:19.521 --> 00:26:20.980
Shouldn't you have one?

00:26:21.563 --> 00:26:24.396
What? You're scared of ghosts?

00:26:26.563 --> 00:26:28.146
That's not it.

00:26:28.730 --> 00:26:31.021
Hey, wait! Wait!

00:26:31.605 --> 00:26:33.605
Wait! Don't leave me alone!

00:27:09.855 --> 00:27:11.021
Let's go.

00:27:25.938 --> 00:27:26.980
108

00:27:35.563 --> 00:27:38.521
We're from the Police Bureau.
Your chief knows we're coming.

00:27:42.313 --> 00:27:44.063
Seems like they took the bait.

00:27:44.646 --> 00:27:46.438
-Huh?
-What's your name, young man?

00:27:48.146 --> 00:27:49.813
I'm Shinnosuke Sayama.

00:27:49.896 --> 00:27:52.021
Shinnosuke, hold these for me.

00:27:52.105 --> 00:27:53.146
Huh?

00:27:53.730 --> 00:27:54.813
Wait!

00:28:00.521 --> 00:28:04.480
The time is 2:17 p.m.
Number 108, Shujiro Saga.

00:28:23.021 --> 00:28:25.521
We're here to examine the suspect
who was just detained.

00:28:25.605 --> 00:28:28.146
Sir, he's in the detention cell
in the basement.

00:28:28.230 --> 00:28:29.438
Let me show you the way.

00:28:37.605 --> 00:28:38.646
Hello, sir.

00:28:43.688 --> 00:28:44.688
Hello.

00:28:45.563 --> 00:28:47.563
I'll join them for the examination.

00:28:48.146 --> 00:28:48.980
Yes, sir.

00:29:44.480 --> 00:29:45.938
Isn't this place…

00:30:10.230 --> 00:30:14.438
At 2:17 p.m. by Kuwana-juku,
number 108, Shujiro Saga was eliminated.

00:32:02.105 --> 00:32:05.730
MITSUI BANK
RECORD OF ALL TRANSACTIONS

00:32:05.813 --> 00:32:07.938
MITSUI BANK
OPENING LOAN AND DEPOSIT LEDGER

00:32:08.438 --> 00:32:10.313
MITSUI BANK GUIDELINES
FOR ESTIMATING WRITE-OFFS

00:32:10.396 --> 00:32:12.146
MITSUI BANK
INTERNAL RULES

00:32:19.355 --> 00:32:20.730
This place is…

00:32:29.896 --> 00:32:31.146
MITSUI BANK

00:32:31.230 --> 00:32:32.438
A bank.

00:32:42.105 --> 00:32:43.271
That guy…

00:33:12.480 --> 00:33:13.938
Are you here to interrogate me?

00:33:15.146 --> 00:33:16.146
Listen to me.

00:33:17.021 --> 00:33:20.688
I didn't kill anybody.
I can explain everything.

00:33:21.271 --> 00:33:24.063
Some crazy people
ordered us to kill each other.

00:33:24.146 --> 00:33:26.105
They threatened to kill us if we escaped.

00:33:26.188 --> 00:33:28.813
Put me under police protection.

00:33:29.396 --> 00:33:32.396
Please. Keep the Kodoku away from me…

00:33:40.355 --> 00:33:41.730
What's going on?

00:33:41.813 --> 00:33:42.855
Wait! No, wait--

00:34:51.146 --> 00:34:52.771
So 108's body is in here?

00:34:52.855 --> 00:34:53.771
Yes, sir.

00:35:28.688 --> 00:35:31.021
Seems that a rat has slipped inside.

00:35:43.563 --> 00:35:45.396
Who's there?

00:35:49.813 --> 00:35:52.396
I'm Takayama
of the Police Bureau's Fourth Division.

00:35:55.146 --> 00:35:58.396
I don't recall any subordinates
with that name.

00:35:59.355 --> 00:36:02.688
Oh, you're from the Police Bureau too…

00:36:04.480 --> 00:36:06.230
You're not fooling anyone.

00:36:09.146 --> 00:36:10.480
Kyojin Tsuge.

00:36:47.646 --> 00:36:49.813
Do you really think you can escape?

00:36:51.646 --> 00:36:52.605
Come now.

00:36:54.146 --> 00:36:56.021
Don't waste time and show yourself.

00:37:01.188 --> 00:37:02.688
Kokushu Saga.

00:37:17.146 --> 00:37:18.605
Hanjiro Nakamura.

00:37:19.688 --> 00:37:21.521
Please, call me Sakura now.

00:37:22.813 --> 00:37:25.188
I saw how Ando was cut down
at Tenryuji Temple.

00:37:25.688 --> 00:37:27.230
I suspected it was you.

00:37:27.313 --> 00:37:30.188
I've been secretly rooting for you.

00:37:30.271 --> 00:37:32.605
I thought you died that day.

00:37:38.896 --> 00:37:42.938
Life is unpredictable, isn't it?

00:37:46.271 --> 00:37:47.188
I…

00:37:48.563 --> 00:37:50.771
I have always looked up to you.

00:37:52.438 --> 00:37:54.188
Just tell me one thing.

00:37:56.480 --> 00:37:58.730
What is it that you are trying to achieve?

00:38:01.188 --> 00:38:03.021
I cannot answer that.

00:38:06.230 --> 00:38:10.813
When two old friends reunite,
they either share drinks together…

00:38:13.563 --> 00:38:14.855
or they kill each other.

00:38:18.105 --> 00:38:19.480
It's one or the other.

00:39:31.813 --> 00:39:36.480
Our analysis shows that the location
they were sending the coded telegrams to

00:39:36.563 --> 00:39:38.605
was the Nihonbashi Telegraph Office.

00:39:39.105 --> 00:39:44.355
So we tracked the individual
who picked up the telegrams…

00:39:45.730 --> 00:39:47.646
and found out where they went.

00:39:49.646 --> 00:39:50.646
Where?

00:39:51.938 --> 00:39:53.813
The final destination…

00:39:57.105 --> 00:39:59.063
was the Home Ministry's Police Bureau.

00:40:15.480 --> 00:40:18.771
Gentlemen.
Apologies for keeping you waiting.

00:40:19.355 --> 00:40:20.980
We've been waiting for you, sir.

00:40:23.146 --> 00:40:25.313
It took you rather long, Organizer.

00:40:25.396 --> 00:40:26.396
Indeed.

00:40:47.313 --> 00:40:48.396
Home Minister.

00:40:49.146 --> 00:40:52.021
I cannot be sure if I should say this…

00:40:56.105 --> 00:40:57.188
What is it?

00:40:59.563 --> 00:41:01.896
Can we really trust Kawaji?

00:41:09.605 --> 00:41:14.271
Once again, I would like to thank you all
for agreeing to this game.

00:41:16.480 --> 00:41:18.730
It's all for the good of this country.

00:41:19.230 --> 00:41:21.521
If it's money you need, don't hesitate.

00:41:21.605 --> 00:41:23.146
Thank you very much.

00:41:26.813 --> 00:41:30.396
Eradicating the specters
is a huge project for our nation.

00:41:31.230 --> 00:41:33.313
A great cause
that we cannot afford to fail.

00:41:35.188 --> 00:41:40.105
Let us be the ones
to fulfill this duty, shall we?

00:41:57.813 --> 00:42:01.063
For the future of this country.

